translation.text: Airport & South Line, Bankstown Line, Inner West & Leppington Line - Delays
due to essential infrastructure repairs at Central. Trains may depart off different platforms at Central. Please listen to announcements & check station indicators before boarding

Delays due to urgent track equipment repairs at Town Hall earlier.  Some services have been cancelled.  Customers may choose to catch Western/ Inner West and Leppington Line services and change trains to complete their journey as an alternative.

Train services are suspended from Wynyard to Central in that direction only due to essential infrastructure repairs at Central. If you are travelling to Town Hall or Central please allow an additional journey time as you will need to change at Wynyard for a train service via the City Circle or a Light Rail service. Please listen to announcements, check indicator boards and plan your trip using Transport Apps.

Delays - urgent track equipment repairs at Town Hall earlier. Some trains to the City will terminate at Central. Some trains from the City will commence from Platforms 1-11 at Central. Please check transport apps for service updates, continue to allow plenty of additional travel time, listen for announcements and check Platform screens before boarding trains.

Please continue to allow plenty of additional journey time when travelling on the Northern line following urgent track equipment repairs at Town Hall earlier. We are working hard to return services to normal, and as a result train stopping patterns and departure platforms may change at short notice; please listen to announcements, check indicator boards, and plan your trip using Transport apps for further information and updates.
Major weekday trackwork - Blue Mountains Line

Blue Mountains Line
Monday 9 to Friday 13 March 
- Due to infrastructure damage caused by bushfires, buses continue to replace trains between Bathurst, Lithgow and Mount Victoria.
- Some trains continue to run between Bathurst and Lithgow, and between Bathurst and Central, to a changed timetable.
- Other trains may also be affected.

Please use Transport Apps or visit transportnsw.info for details.

The lift between the concourse and Harvey Road is temporarily out of service.
The lift between the concourse and bus bay E is temporarily out of service. If you require assistance, please ask staff or phone 9765 1161.
The lift between the concourse and the northern carpark on Railway Terrace is temporarily out of service. For assistance ask station staff or call 9851 7244.
The lift between the concourse and Railway Street is temporarily out of service. For assistance ask staff or call 9851 7243.

Drop-off zones on Kirkham Road alongside platform 1 will not be accessible until June due to scheduled council roadworks. An alternative drop-off zone is available at the Station Car Park located on Station Street.  Please allow additional time in order to catch your service.

The public toilets at St James Station are closed while major works are taking place. Public toilets are located at the Elizabeth Street entrance to the right and in Hyde Park through the Macquarie Street tunnel up the stairs to the right. We apologise for any inconvenience.

New Metro Platforms are being constructed on platforms 1 & 2 at Sydenham Station. T3 Bankstown Line services to the City operate from platform 3 & T3 Bankstown Line services to Lidcombe and Liverpool operate from platform 4. Platform 4, 5 & 6 upgrade works - A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5. If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info

Station Upgrade - Customers, due to Wynyard station upgrade the lifts from the concourse level to George Street will be closed until July 2020. Customers will be able use alternate lifts from Wynyard Station to Carrington Street and York Street accessed via Margaret Street.  For further information or assistance, Please follow station staff instructions, station signage or call Wynyard Station on 9224 2959.
